0.8a
Java Version
changed target version 1.7 to 1.8

Bugs
-ui refreshes now also when only the target or source of operations change status
-operation time (instead of 0) is now displayed in synchronization process dialog
-Restoration failed in a certain case, should not anymore
-Conflict management for bidirectional synchronization was broken
-tray menu items are disabled now when running a synchronization from tray
-fixed disappearing gui glitch when minimizing the main frame during the display of a modal dialog

Improvements
-circular relations are not allowed anymore
-segment operations are being sorted now too
-source directory safety improved (windows)
-synchronization process dialog can now x-ed after the synchronization process has ended
-remind for new version dialog can be suppressed
-warning upon if this executable is ran after a newer version was executed
-only one instance is allowed to be running
-optional deleting of databases when deleting operation

Changes
-When data integrity seems compromised no further actions are taken
-Access to Restore functionality is new available via a special dialog
-When Copying a file results in an error the file is skipped and the process continues
-progress bar now loads the average analysis and synchronization time
-removed segments menu and added "add segment" and segments to edit menu
-removed ignore modification time when files are equal

New Features
-Operation option: quick synchronization
-Operation option: Elastic time comparison (+/- 1 sec)
-Restore Selection Dialog
-Operation Statistics

0.7a
Bugs
-fixed entering file data in database before successful copying

Improvements
-Quickinfo/Tooltip on ui diagram clickable items
-fall back algorithm in case the database is out of sync with the fs
-made opening from tray open with single click

New Features
-check for new version on startup

0.6a
Bugs
